                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.972,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has our opinion in Case 14-103, Baker Botts v. ASARCO."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 7.972,
                        "stop": 182.112,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15100,
                            "name": "Clarence Thomas",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/clarence_thomas",
                            "last_name": "Thomas",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2744,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 688194000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2744"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32680,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49064,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/clarence_thomas.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8870,
                            "identifier": "clarence_thomas"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 7.972,
                                "stop": 14.527,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on a writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.527,
                                "stop": 37.722,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In 2005, respondent ASARCO LLC, copper mining company, filed for Chapter 11 Bankruptcy. As in many Chapter 11 Bankruptcies no trustee was appointed and ASARCO, the debtor-in-possession, administered the bankruptcy estate."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 37.722,
                                "stop": 49.503,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "ASARCO got the bankruptcy court\u0027s permission to hire two law firms, petitioners here, to assist in carrying out its duties of administering the estate."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 49.503,
                                "stop": 58.766,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "After ASARCO emerged from bankruptcy, those firms filed fee applications seeking compensation for their work."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 58.766,
                                "stop": 72.087,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "ASARCO challenged the request, but the Bankruptcy Court overruled their objections and awarded the firm\u0027s attorney\u0027s fees for their work in the bankruptcy proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 72.087,
                                "stop": 78.722,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It also awarded them fees for time spent litigating in defense of their fee applications."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 78.722,
                                "stop": 83.49,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The District Court affirmed the defense award."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 83.49,
                                "stop": 93.814,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But the Fifth Circuit reversed concluding that the Bankruptcy Code does not allow courts to award fees for time spent defending fee applications."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 93.814,
                                "stop": 99.692,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the clerk today we affirm the judgment of the Fifth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 99.692,
                                "stop": 105.862,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Under what is known as the American Rule each side pays its own attorney\u0027s fees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.862,
                                "stop": 112.065,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That rule applies unless a statute explicitly says otherwise."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.065,
                                "stop": 125.391,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "And here the relevant statute, Section 330(a)(1) of the Bankruptcy Code, does not expressly deviate from the American Rule with respect to fee defense litigation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 125.391,
                                "stop": 136.121,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Section 330(a)(1) allows courts to award \u201creasonable compensation for actual, necessary services rendered\u201d."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 136.121,
                                "stop": 152.599,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The word services refers to labor performed for another, and time spent litigating a fee application against the administrator of a bankruptcy estate cannot fairly be described as labor performed for that administrator."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 152.599,
                                "stop": 161.198,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Section 330(a)(1) thus does not depart from the American Rule with respect to fee defense litigation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 161.198,
                                "stop": 167.691,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "For these reasons and others set forth in our opinion, we affirm the judgment of the Fifth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 167.691,
                                "stop": 174.219,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Sotomayor has filed an opinion concurring in part and concurring in the judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 174.219,
                                "stop": 182.112,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Breyer has filed a dissenting opinion, in which Justices Ginsburg and Kagan have joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
